    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-11T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="355"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d355">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/3617: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-11T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 11, 1919, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>189. For Secretary of State.</p>
                <p>Your 209 January 9, noon. I agree thoroughly with your views, but believe it is
                    essential; first, to define our attitude towards the Bolsheviki; second, then to
                    state how far the associated governments are prepared and able to go in
                    supporting elements of law and order; third, what funds for military supplies
                    have you in mind from which this government could supply financial aid.</p>
                <p>I know you appreciate that the whole Russian situation requires a clear
                    definition by the associated governments and that time presses. The first step
                    is the railways and I am waiting to hear whether <persName corresp="#p_SJF1"
                        >Stevens</persName> can have any cooperation from <persName
                        corresp="#p_GMGWS1">General Graves</persName> before I instruct him and
                    Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_MRS1">Morris</persName> to put plan in
                        operation.<note n="46" xml:id="d355fn46">See section on the Inter-Allied
                        Agreement for Supervision of the Chinese Eastern and the Siberian Railways,
                            <ref target="#pg_236">pp. 236</ref> ff.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
